<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="1798" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1798">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 823.00/121.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">McMillin</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-08">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 8, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>First Vice President has been out of Peru for many months; Second Vice
                            President has resigned, leaving no official of old government to assume
                            or claim the right to executive power in the new. No other change in the
                            situation since my last. The question of recognition is now being raised
                            by other legations and am informed that in certain cases only they await
                            American action. Papal Legate and Italian, Brazilian and Argentine
                            Ministers favor recognition. French Minister undecided. No evidence of
                            organized opposition to present régime, nor does any seem probable.
                            Believe ultimate recognition inevitable. Request instruction.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">McMillin</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>